  "prompt": "Naruto (creative franchise): Why is Jiraiya's headband different from that of other Leaf Shinobi?",
  "response": "In the Naruto franchise, Jiraiya wears a unique headband that differs from the standard Leaf Village (Konoha) headband. While most Konoha shinobi wear their headband with the village symbol (a stylized leaf) displayed prominently and tied around their forehead, Jiraiya typically wears his headband tied around his neck instead. This unconventional style reflects his rebellious and somewhat independent nature as a legendary ninja who often operates outside traditional norms. Despite not wearing it in the typical manner, Jiraiya remains deeply loyal to Konoha and is considered one of the village's most respected ninja.",
